## 9. Theoretical Justification Summary

The complete theoretical chain:

$$\text{Cover time bound: } E[C(G)] \leq \frac{n}{2} \cdot \frac{\ln n}{\lambda_2}(1+o(1))$$

$$\Downarrow$$

$$\text{Maximize } \lambda_2 \text{ by greedily adding edges between } \arg\max f \text{ and } \arg\min f$$

$$\Downarrow$$

$$\text{Each added edge = an option/macro connecting distant UI states}$$

$$\Downarrow$$

$$\text{Reduced cover time } \Rightarrow \text{ faster exploration } \Rightarrow \text{ faster convergence of RL/SFT}$$

The deep covering options objective function (Eq. 5) is an unconstrained approximation of the covering options objective, which has **provable guarantees** on cover time reduction. The approximation enables scaling to large state spaces via neural network parameterization while preserving the theoretical motivation.

